Description

This lab contains a path traversal vulnerability in the product image functionality. The application attempts to sanitize input by stripping traversal sequences, but the filtering is flawed and can be bypassed using crafted input.

Objective

Retrieve the contents of the /etc/passwd file.

Steps to Solve
Intercept the request using Burp Suite while loading a product image.
Identify the parameter used to specify the image file (e.g., filename).

Modify the filename parameter to bypass the filter:

....//....//....//etc/passwd
Send the modified request to the server.
Observe that the response contains the contents of the /etc/passwd file.
Conclusion

The application’s input sanitization is insufficient and can be bypassed using alternative traversal patterns. This allows attackers to access sensitive files outside the intended directory.
